Boring couple of days for the most part. Yesterday went to the Dr's. Didnt even get to see him bc they were so backed up. Then went and got my hair cut and colored. It is officially BLONDE now. No more highlights. Just blonde. It looks good too. And i lost a bunch of more weight. So I am looking good. Very very good, but always room for improvement. Stopped by work last night to visit Jess and eat some dinner. Then went to a CAPS psychology seminar on eating disorders and body image for my psych class. Not a good idea, not at all, considering i just ate right before it. Made me wanna go vomit my food. Ewww. HAHA. Fought with Bobby last night. I hope we work out, but I just dont know. 6 more months to go before he moves back up here. I wish the drama would just end. Then watched "Fear" with jess in my bed last night. YAY I had Jess in my bed. She took good care of me yesterday. She's an awsome friend. Then I fell asleep.

Woke up today and went to the DR. again, but at least this time he saw me. I have a heart murmur. And the reason i get so dizzy and nauseous is bc my blood pressure keeps dropping really low. They need to do some more investigated on it. I get to go next wed to get a heart monitor for 24 hours. Gonna be fun dragging that thing around with me. Then off to have an ultra sound done on my heart. Woo. Means i need to stop smoking. I'm gonna be a wonderful person to be around. lol. oh well. No serious excerice until they do all the testing, so that should be fun. 

Got new body jewelery this week. YAY for Jess sticking her fingers down my throat trying to put my tongue ring in. HAHA. She's so good to me. And it's almost my birthday. Still no definate plans yet, most likely typhoon lagoon or wet-n-wild on Sunday with Donnielle and friends, but still not sure. Then on my actual b-day, no plans. Just school and taking a test. Sounds super right??? Then definately going to the beach or something if it is nice. Gotta keep up the tan to go with my new blonde hair. HAHA

Well I guess I wrote enough for now. TTYL!
